Operators: List of owners of submarine cable infrastructure separated by comma
Known Users (ASes): List of ASes known to purchase space on submarine cables separated by comma. If same as operators, left blank.
Length of Cable System (km): Length of entire cable system over all segments
Sources: List of web pages used to gather information separated by comma.
Connecting cables: Name of the secondary cable system that connects to the cable system (for an example of what this looks like, refer to tata-tgn-gulf and SEACOM)
Landing Point 1: Landing point 1 City, Country. If landing point is in US, two letter state code appears after city and before comma (ex. New York City NY, US). NOTE: will not be 18 landing points for most cables. Segment data starts after 18 LP columns
Segment 1: City, Country end points of cable segment 1 in following format: city1, country1; city2, country 2
Segment 1 Length (km): Length of cable segment 1 in km. If length is not available, left blank.
Segment 1 Predicted RTT (ms): Officially reported expected RTT of cable segment
Segment 2: If segment connects to another segment rather than a landing point, format it as follows:[segment1city1, segment1country1; segment1city2,segment1country2]; segment2city, segment2country
